<title>Actions</title>

<p>All changes made using blivet-gui are only temporary. They won't be written to disks until <em>apply</em>.</p>

<p>List of currently scheduled actions is avaialbe under <gui>Pending actions</gui> tab.</p>

<figure>
  <title>Pending actions</title>
  <media type="image" src="images/pending-actions.png" width="400" />
</figure>

<section id="apply">
    <title>Apply queued actions</title>

<p>To apply all queued actions and write all changes to disks, click <gui>Apply</gui> button in the toolbar.
All scheduled changes will be made. According to number and type of actions and size of created partitions/devices, it may take several minutes.</p> 
    
</section>

<section id="clear">
    <title>Clear queued actions</title>

<p>To cancel all queued actions, click <gui>Clear</gui> button on the toolbar.
All scheduled changes will be dropped.</p> 

<note>
  <p>Currently is not possible to delete/undo last action or to manage actions in more detailed way. This feature is planned for blivet-gui 0.2.0.</p>
</note>
    
</section>

